17657594","html_url":"https://github.com/gabime/spdlog/issues/1176#issuecomment-517657594","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gabime/spdlog/issues/1176","id":517657594,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDUxNzY1NzU5NA==","user":{"login":"artemyv","id":24264210,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0MjY0MjEw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24264210?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv","html_url":"https://github.com/artemyv","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-08-02T10:53:42Z","updated_at":"2019-08-02T11:04:45Z","body":"How about adding possibility to log mix of wide and narrow string arguments using narrow format when SPDLOG_WCHAR_TO_UTF8_SUPPORT is on?\r\n\r\nBasic idea would be to convert all wide strings to narrow before passing to force_log instead of current approach of the whole buffer only. Will this require to much overhead?\r\n\r\n```c++\r\n\t#include \"spdlog/spdlog.h\"\r\n\r\n\t#define SPDLOG_LOGGER_CALL_W(logger, level, ...)    logline(logger,spdlog::source_loc{__FILE__, __LINE__, SPDLOG_FUNCTION}, level, __VA_ARGS__)\r\n\r\n\ttemplate<class T>\r\n\tauto convert(T&& arg)\r\n\t{\r\n\t\treturn std::forward<T>(arg); // Forward as lvalue or as rvalue, depending on T\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tauto convert(const wchar_t* arg)\r\n\t{\r\n\t\tauto result_size = ::WideCharToMultiByte(CP_UTF8, 0, arg, -1, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL);\r\n\r\n\t\tif (result_size > 0)\r\n\t\t{\r\n\t\t\tstd::string target;\r\n\t\t\ttarget.resize(result_size);\r\n\t\t\tresult_size = ::WideCharToMultiByte(CP_UTF8, 0, arg, -1, target.data(), result_size, NULL, NULL);\r\n\r\n\t\t\tif (result_size > 0)\r\n\t\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\ttarget.resize(result_size);\r\n\t\t\t\treturn target;\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tthrow std::exception(\"Could not convert string\");\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\ttemplate<typename LoggerPtr, typename... Ts>\r\n\tvoid logline(LoggerPtr logger, spdlog::source_loc loc, spdlog::level::level_enum level, const char* fmt, Ts... args)\r\n\t{\r\n\t\tif (logger->should_log(level))                                                                                                     \r\n\t\t\tlogger->force_log(loc, level, fmt, convert(args)...);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tint main(int, char*[])\r\n\t{\r\n\t\tspdlog::info(\"Welcome to spdlog version {}.{}.{}  !\", SPDLOG_VER_MAJOR, SPDLOG_VER_MINOR, SPDLOG_VER_PATCH);\r\n\t\tspdlog::info(L\"{}\", L\"This message should be displayed..\");\r\n\t\tSPDLOG_LOGGER_CALL_W(spdlog::default_logger_raw(),spdlog::level::info,\"{} is {}\", L\"This message should be displayed..\", \"This message should be displayed..\");\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI did not try to utilize details::os::wstr_to_utf8buf as is to to provide sample for all possible string representations just a general idea.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gabime/spdlog/issues/comments/517657594/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"artemyv","id":24264210,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0MjY0MjEw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24264210?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv","html_url":"https://github.com/artemyv","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artemyv/followers","